**Key finding (final treatment-effect heterogeneity hypothesis):** feature_008 is the favorable binary treatment. Its absolute effect on `objective_response` is +0.626 (response 0.798 vs 0.172) in patients meeting all four predicates `feature_013=0 AND feature_015=0 AND feature_021=0 AND feature_027=0` (n = 15,681), and null (|diff| < 0.02, all p > 0.07) in any patient violating any one of those predicates. Each predicate is necessary. Equivalently, each of feature_015, feature_021, feature_027 individually abolishes the favorable feature_008 effect within the (f013=0, f008=1) responsive cell. feature_001 acts as a global monotone prognostic, and feature_022/020/024 (negative) and feature_002 (positive) contribute small independent log-odds effects.
